 own.Her dresses now wear their own selves, her books leaf through their ownpages. We suffocate in the tightening circle of those monsters that aremisplaced and misshapen because she is not there to tend them. And even thebravest among us cannot meet the gaze of her mirror.

How to get rid of them is another problem. I could not drown them likekittens; in fact, I could not drown a kitten, let alone her brush or bag.Nor could I watch a stranger collect them, take them away, come back formore. The